# 💻 BMI Calculator (Advanced GUI Version)

This project is part of the **Oasis Infobyte Python Internship**.  
It’s an **advanced version of the BMI Calculator** built with **Tkinter (Python GUI library)**.  
The app allows users to enter their weight and height through a simple interface and instantly see their BMI result and category.

---

## 🚀 How to Run

1. Ensure you have **Python 3.x** installed.
2. Save the file as `gui_bmi_calculator.py`.
3. Run the program using:

   ```bash
   python gui_bmi_calculator.py
A window will open where you can input:

Weight (in kilograms)

Height (in meters)

Click the “Calculate BMI” button to see your result.

⚙️ Features
Graphical User Interface using Tkinter 🪟

Automatic BMI calculation and category classification

Input validation with error messages

Clean, simple, and user-friendly layout

